Classes in de.bpmnaftool.model.aristaflow.graph.node that implement Node
 class AndJoinNode
          An AndJoinNode is used to close branches.
 class AndSplitNode
          An AndJoinSplit is used to start a new branch.
 class EndFlowNode
          Special node which is used as the only leave of the tree graph (last node).
 class EndLoopNode
          This node may have an XOR Activity assigned which contains a condition for the do-until loop.
 class NodeImpl
          Implementation base class for all types of nodes
 class NormalNode
          A normal node is a typical workflow activity, however this is just a node in a graph - it may or may not have an activity assigned.
 class StartFlowNode
          Special node which is used as the root of the tree graph (first node).
 class StartLoopNode
          This node may have an XOR Activity assigned which contains a condition for the do-until loop.
 class XorJoinNode
          An XorJoinNode is used to close branches.
 class XorSplitNode
          An XorSplitNode is used to start a new branch.
